            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I am writing this as a teacher who has worked there for 12 months. I wish i could give them 0 stars.\nI am sharing this as a serious warning to parents considering Proxima International School. Based on direct experience and interactions with teachers and staff, the school does not provide the quality of education or facilities it promises.\n\nThere is a shortage of qualified teachers, frequent staff turnover, and reports of teachers not being paid salaries on time, which directly affects students’ learning and stability. The school also lacks basic infrastructure and essential facilities expected from a reputed institution.\n\nManagement appears poorly organized and prioritizes frequent functions and events where money is collected from parents, while basic needs of children—such as proper classrooms, resources, and teaching support—are neglected. Transparency with parents is very limited.\n\nParents are advised to verify all claims carefully, speak to current parents and teachers, and personally inspect facilities before enrolling their children. The well-being and education of children should come first, and unfortunately this school falls short of that responsibility.",
